/*
 * ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  GOOGLE AUTHENTICATION SET-UP INSTRUCTIONS
 * ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * 1. Go to the Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
 * 2. Create a new Firebase project (or select an existing one).
 * 3. Inside the project, click “Add app” ➜ choose “Android”.
 * 4. Register your package name, SHA-1 debug / release fingerprints, etc.
 * 5. Download the generated `google-services.json` file.
 * 6. Replace THIS file (`app/google-services.json`) with the downloaded file.
 * 7. ALSO open Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials
 *    (https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials)
 *    • Click “Create Credentials → OAuth client ID”.
 *    • Choose “Android”, enter the same package name and SHA-1 fingerprint,
 *      then click “Create”.
 * 8. Sync / rebuild the project. Google Authentication will now work.
 * ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 */

